{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01WGgg9fUhqnqCjdED2b1nUj","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! I have both files. Let me provide you with a thorough analysis of the auth verify route and its dependencies.\n\n## Summary\n\n### AuthRoutesDeps Interface\n\nLocated in `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/routes/auth.ts` (lines 13-20):\n\n```typescript\nexport interface AuthRoutesDeps {\n  authDb: AuthDb;\n  jwtSecret: Uint8Array;\n  cluster: string;\n  challengeTtlSeconds: number;\n  accessTokenTtlSeconds: number;\n  refreshTokenTtlDays: number;\n}\n```\n\nThis is a clean interface with 6 properties. Notably, **`db` (the game database) is NOT included** in AuthRoutesDeps — only `authDb` is. The auth system is completely separated from the main game database.\n\n---\n\n### POST /verify Handler (Lines 93-184)\n\nThe verify endpoint performs signature verification over the challenge message. Here's the full flow:\n\n**1. Request parsing** (lines 94-106):\n- Accepts JSON with `nonce`, `wallet`, and `signature` (all strings)\n- Returns 400 if any field is missing or invalid JSON\n\n**2. Challenge consumption** (lines 108-116):\n- Atomically consumes the challenge with `authDb.consumeChallenge(body.nonce)`\n- If no challenge exists, expired, or already used → returns 401\n- This is atomic, preventing replay attacks\n\n**3. Wallet validation** (lines 118-126):\n- Verifies that `challenge.wallet === body.wallet`\n- If mismatch → returns 401\n\n**4. Ed25519 signature verification** (lines 128-149):\n- Decodes signature and wallet from base58 encoding\n- Validates lengths: signature = 64 bytes, pubkey = 32 bytes\n- Uses **nacl.sign.detached.verify()** to verify the signature over the challenge message\n- Message is UTF-8 encoded, signature and pubkey are decoded from base58\n- If verification fails → returns 401\n\n**5. JWT access token issuance** (lines 151-159):\n- Creates a JWT with subject = wallet address\n- Uses HS256 algorithm with `jwtSecret`\n- Expiration time = current time + `accessTokenTtlSeconds`\n\n**6. Refresh token issuance** (lines 161-174):\n- Generates 48-byte random refresh token (hex-encoded)\n- Hashes it with SHA256 for storage (via `hashToken()`)\n- Creates a family ID (16-byte random hex) for token rotation tracking\n- Stores in `authDb.insertRefreshToken()` with wallet, hash, family ID, and expiry\n\n**7. Success response** (lines 178-183):\n```typescript\n{\n  accessToken: string,\n  accessExpiresAt: ISO 8601 string,\n  refreshToken: string (raw, unhashed),\n  refreshExpiresAt: ISO 8601 string\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### How Dependencies Are Constructed and Passed\n\nIn `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/index.ts` (lines 81-91):\n\n```typescript\napp.route(\n  \"/auth\",\n  createAuthRoutes({\n    authDb,\n    jwtSecret: config.jwtSecret,\n    cluster: config.cluster,\n    challengeTtlSeconds: config.challengeTtlSeconds,\n    accessTokenTtlSeconds: config.accessTokenTtlSeconds,\n    refreshTokenTtlDays: config.refreshTokenTtlDays,\n  }),\n);\n```\n\nAll dependencies are constructed from:\n- **Line 36**: `const authDb = createAuthDb(sql);` — created from the postgres pool\n- **Lines 31-34**: Config values loaded via `loadConfig()` at startup\n- These are then passed to `createAuthRoutes()` which returns a Hono app\n\n---\n\n### How `db` is Available in the Codebase\n\n**Game database `db` is NOT passed to auth routes.** Looking at index.ts:\n\n- **Line 35**: `const db = createDb(config.databaseUrl, sql);` — created at startup\n- **Line 36**: `const authDb = createAuthDb(sql);` — separate auth-specific database layer\n\nThe game `db` is used in other routes:\n- Line 98: `createProfileRoutes({ db })`\n- Line 105: `createReferralRoutes({ db, sql, config })`\n- Line 204: `createCoinflipRoutes({ db, connection, serverKeypair, pdaWatcher })`\n\n**To add `db` to auth routes, you would need to:**\n1. Add `db: Database` to the `AuthRoutesDeps` interface (line 14 in auth.ts)\n2. Destructure it in `createAuthRoutes()` (line 46)\n3. Pass it when registering routes in index.ts (line 83)\n\nThe `db` and `authDb` are both created from the same postgres pool (`sql`), so they can operate on the same database server without conflicts."}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c90b48a1-f03a-4fbb-962c-9618a8223eda","uuid":"62faa84c-1b8d-4dcb-b90e-2d50f13f3006","timestamp":"2026-03-31T14:56:06.035Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"I need to understand the auth verify route in the backend. Read these files thoroughly:\n\n1. `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/routes/auth.ts` — the full file\n2. `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/index.ts` — particularly how routes are registered and what deps are passed\n\nI need to know:\n- The AuthRoutesDeps interface\n- The POST /verify handler (where signature verification happens)\n- How deps are constructed and passed when registering auth routes\n- How `db` is available in the codebase (is it already part of deps or do I need to add it?)\n\nReport the full contents of relevant code sections, especially the verify handler and the deps interface. Be thorough.","agentId":"a49dc20fdd1425cc4","agentType":"Explore","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! I have both files. Let me provide you with a thorough analysis of the auth verify route and its dependencies.\n\n## Summary\n\n### AuthRoutesDeps Interface\n\nLocated in `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/routes/auth.ts` (lines 13-20):\n\n```typescript\nexport interface AuthRoutesDeps {\n  authDb: AuthDb;\n  jwtSecret: Uint8Array;\n  cluster: string;\n  challengeTtlSeconds: number;\n  accessTokenTtlSeconds: number;\n  refreshTokenTtlDays: number;\n}\n```\n\nThis is a clean interface with 6 properties. Notably, **`db` (the game database) is NOT included** in AuthRoutesDeps — only `authDb` is. The auth system is completely separated from the main game database.\n\n---\n\n### POST /verify Handler (Lines 93-184)\n\nThe verify endpoint performs signature verification over the challenge message. Here's the full flow:\n\n**1. Request parsing** (lines 94-106):\n- Accepts JSON with `nonce`, `wallet`, and `signature` (all strings)\n- Returns 400 if any field is missing or invalid JSON\n\n**2. Challenge consumption** (lines 108-116):\n- Atomically consumes the challenge with `authDb.consumeChallenge(body.nonce)`\n- If no challenge exists, expired, or already used → returns 401\n- This is atomic, preventing replay attacks\n\n**3. Wallet validation** (lines 118-126):\n- Verifies that `challenge.wallet === body.wallet`\n- If mismatch → returns 401\n\n**4. Ed25519 signature verification** (lines 128-149):\n- Decodes signature and wallet from base58 encoding\n- Validates lengths: signature = 64 bytes, pubkey = 32 bytes\n- Uses **nacl.sign.detached.verify()** to verify the signature over the challenge message\n- Message is UTF-8 encoded, signature and pubkey are decoded from base58\n- If verification fails → returns 401\n\n**5. JWT access token issuance** (lines 151-159):\n- Creates a JWT with subject = wallet address\n- Uses HS256 algorithm with `jwtSecret`\n- Expiration time = current time + `accessTokenTtlSeconds`\n\n**6. Refresh token issuance** (lines 161-174):\n- Generates 48-byte random refresh token (hex-encoded)\n- Hashes it with SHA256 for storage (via `hashToken()`)\n- Creates a family ID (16-byte random hex) for token rotation tracking\n- Stores in `authDb.insertRefreshToken()` with wallet, hash, family ID, and expiry\n\n**7. Success response** (lines 178-183):\n```typescript\n{\n  accessToken: string,\n  accessExpiresAt: ISO 8601 string,\n  refreshToken: string (raw, unhashed),\n  refreshExpiresAt: ISO 8601 string\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### How Dependencies Are Constructed and Passed\n\nIn `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/index.ts` (lines 81-91):\n\n```typescript\napp.route(\n  \"/auth\",\n  createAuthRoutes({\n    authDb,\n    jwtSecret: config.jwtSecret,\n    cluster: config.cluster,\n    challengeTtlSeconds: config.challengeTtlSeconds,\n    accessTokenTtlSeconds: config.accessTokenTtlSeconds,\n    refreshTokenTtlDays: config.refreshTokenTtlDays,\n  }),\n);\n```\n\nAll dependencies are constructed from:\n- **Line 36**: `const authDb = createAuthDb(sql);` — created from the postgres pool\n- **Lines 31-34**: Config values loaded via `loadConfig()` at startup\n- These are then passed to `createAuthRoutes()` which returns a Hono app\n\n---\n\n### How `db` is Available in the Codebase\n\n**Game database `db` is NOT passed to auth routes.** Looking at index.ts:\n\n- **Line 35**: `const db = createDb(config.databaseUrl, sql);` — created at startup\n- **Line 36**: `const authDb = createAuthDb(sql);` — separate auth-specific database layer\n\nThe game `db` is used in other routes:\n- Line 98: `createProfileRoutes({ db })`\n- Line 105: `createReferralRoutes({ db, sql, config })`\n- Line 204: `createCoinflipRoutes({ db, connection, serverKeypair, pdaWatcher })`\n\n**To add `db` to auth routes, you would need to:**\n1. Add `db: Database` to the `AuthRoutesDeps` interface (line 14 in auth.ts)\n2. Destructure it in `createAuthRoutes()` (line 46)\n3. Pass it when registering routes in index.ts (line 83)\n\nThe `db` and `authDb` are both created from the same postgres pool (`sql`), so they can operate on the same database server without conflicts."}],"totalDurationMs":14769,"totalTokens":35986,"totalToolUseCount":2,"usage":{"input_tokens":7,"cache_creation_input_tokens":8968,"cache_read_input_tokens":25786,"output_tokens":1225,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":8968},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
