{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01BpJwEJdGMLSSiqk6Q5xEna","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Here's a comprehensive summary of the player profile DB functions in `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/db.ts`:\n\n## PlayerProfile Type Definition\n**Lines 186–196:**\n```typescript\nexport interface PlayerProfile {\n  id: number;\n  user_id: string;\n  wallet: string;\n  username: string;\n  username_updated_at: Date | null;\n  avatar_url: string | null;\n  heat_multiplier: number;\n  points_balance: number;\n  created_at: Date;\n}\n```\n\n## createPlayerProfile Function\n**Lines 1023–1052:**\n```typescript\nasync createPlayerProfile(wallet: string): Promise<PlayerProfile>\n```\n- Generates a new user_id and attempts to generate a random username\n- Retries up to 5 times on username collision (handles UNIQUE violations)\n- Falls back to `user-{random8}` format if all retries exhausted\n- Returns a normalized PlayerProfile\n- Throws on non-collision errors or after exhausting retries\n\n## getProfileByWallet Function\n**Lines 1054–1059:**\n```typescript\nasync getProfileByWallet(wallet: string): Promise<PlayerProfile | null>\n```\n- Queries the `player_profiles` table for a matching wallet address\n- Returns the normalized PlayerProfile or null if not found\n\n## Db Interface — Player Profile Methods\n**Lines 429–449:** The interface exposes three player profile-related methods:\n\n1. **createPlayerProfile(wallet: string): Promise<PlayerProfile>** (line 433)\n   - Create a new player profile with auto-generated user_id and username\n   - Retries up to 5 times on username collision, then falls back to `user-{random8}`\n\n2. **getProfileByWallet(wallet: string): Promise<PlayerProfile | null>** (line 436)\n   - Get a player profile by wallet address\n   - Returns null if not found\n\n3. **getProfileByIdentifier(identifier: string): Promise<PlayerProfile | null>** (line 443)\n   - Get a player profile by public identifier (user_id or username)\n   - If identifier starts with `usr_`, looks up by user_id\n   - Otherwise looks up by username (case-insensitive)\n\nAdditional related method:\n4. **updateUsername(wallet: string, newUsername: string): Promise<PlayerProfile>** (line 449)\n   - Update a player's username with 30-day cooldown validation\n   - First edit is free, subsequent edits must wait 30 days\n   - Throws on cooldown violation or UNIQUE conflict\n\nThese are the exact signatures you need to call from your auth route."}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c90b48a1-f03a-4fbb-962c-9618a8223eda","uuid":"0329b5e2-5641-4a26-a27e-5888d2a23184","timestamp":"2026-03-31T14:56:12.228Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"I need to see the existing player profile DB functions in `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/db.ts`. Specifically:\n\n1. The `PlayerProfile` type definition\n2. The `createPlayerProfile` function\n3. The `getProfileByWallet` function\n4. The `Db` interface — what methods does it expose?\n\nSearch for these in the file and report the relevant code sections with line numbers. I need to understand the exact function signatures to call them from the auth route.","agentId":"a4b84cfa99fcd335e","agentType":"Explore","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Here's a comprehensive summary of the player profile DB functions in `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/db.ts`:\n\n## PlayerProfile Type Definition\n**Lines 186–196:**\n```typescript\nexport interface PlayerProfile {\n  id: number;\n  user_id: string;\n  wallet: string;\n  username: string;\n  username_updated_at: Date | null;\n  avatar_url: string | null;\n  heat_multiplier: number;\n  points_balance: number;\n  created_at: Date;\n}\n```\n\n## createPlayerProfile Function\n**Lines 1023–1052:**\n```typescript\nasync createPlayerProfile(wallet: string): Promise<PlayerProfile>\n```\n- Generates a new user_id and attempts to generate 